From 67b7a22492dbbc58cb8db1eca3ddd0305c7916ad Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <pham.francesco@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Mar 2026 12:37:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] init: add support for running within LXC containers

- Added InContainerMode() utility to detect containerized environments via 'container' env var.
- Modified main.c to skip SystemPrepare (first-stage init) when running in a container.
- Updated device.c to skip basic filesystem mounting and device node creation in container mode.
- Patched init_cmds.c to skip mount_fstab, umount_fstab, insmod, and restorecon in containers.
- Updated standard/init.c to skip settimeofday, cgroup sync, and SELinux loading in containers.
- Fixed LogInit to attempt opening /dev/kmsg even if mknod fails.
- Modified ueventd to exit early when running inside a container.
- Fixed a typo in init_common_service.c (#ExecReboot -> ExecReboot).

Change-Id: Id802f66c20ec339ddac7877b6724c56d5405a880
